{"lemma":"زَكاةٍ","slug":"زَكاةٍ","root":"ز.ك.#","root_slug":"ز-ك-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-ك-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"زَكاة","root":"زكو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":32},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17915","n17932","n17936"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"zakat, almsgiving (one of the five pillars of Islam)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"purification from excess, to free from inefficiencies, to dispense filth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"purifying (of the soul)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"purifying (of the soul); in piety, in purity","tags":["adverbial"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Normalized spelling of earlier زَكَوٰة (zakāh), from Aramaic זכותא / ܙܟܘܬܐ (zākūṯā) otherwise attested in the senses of “merit”, “gain; victory” from base stem זכי (zəḵē, “to overcome; to triumph over; to gain”) but not in the sense of “alms”, however in the geminate stem in Jewish Palestinian Aramaic זכי (zakkē) also as “to give possession”, “to give merit” and ultimately “to give charity”. Likewise the noun is not attested but can be inferred from Arabic to have borne in Aramaic the sense of “purity or purification from guilt” as in Palestinian Aramaic the base and geminate stems meant “to be innocent” and “to judge innocent” respectively.\nThe Arabic root ز ك و (z k w) is in part from this noun."},"ipa":["/za.kaːh/","/zəˈkaːt/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17915","headword_ar":"زَكَاَهُ","root":"zkA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zako'N","text_ar":"زَكْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He paid it in ready money, quickly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"promptly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prompt, in doing so."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S.) [The verb is doubly trans. in this sense:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA^ahu A^alofFA","text_ar":"زَكَاَهُ اَلْفًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He paid him a thousand"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning a thousand dirhems, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in ready money, quickly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"promptly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA^otuhu Haq~ahu","text_ar":"زَكَاْتُهُ حَقَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I paid him his due;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakaA^otuhu Hq~h","text_ar":"نَكَاْتُهُ حقّه"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nako'N","text_ar":"نَكْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISh, TA) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA^ati Aln~aAqapu biwaladihaA","text_ar":"زَكَاَتِ النَّاقَةُ بِوَلَدِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-camel cast forth her young one at her hind legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hind feet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, and so in some copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at her hind leg,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hind foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in other copies of the K:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in labour, cast forth her young one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA.) And one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaHa","text_ar":"قَبَحَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu A^um~FA zakaA^ato bihi","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ اُمًّا زَكَاَتْ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lakaA^otu bh","text_ar":"لَكَاْتُ به"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God remove from good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperity, a mother that cast him forth from her womb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that brought him forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA^ahu","text_ar":"زَكَاَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, (K,) and so the inf. n., (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He beat him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"struck him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) So in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA^ahu miAy^apa sawoTK","text_ar":"زَكَاَهُ مِايَةَ سَوْطٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He beat him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"struck him, with a hundred stripes of the whip"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA^a jaAriyatahu","text_ar":"زَكَاَ جَارِيَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He compressed his young woman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female slave."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA^a A_ilayohi","text_ar":"زَكَاَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had recourse to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, for refuge, protection, preservation, concealment, covert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lodging; he leaned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stayed himself, upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","ISh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n17932","headword_ar":"زكّاهُ","root":"zkw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazokiyapN","text_ar":"تَزْكِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He purified him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.) Sometimes the agent of the verb in this sense is a man; as in the saying in the Kur [xci. 9],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado A^afolaHa mano","text_ar":"قَدْ اَفْلَحَ مَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zak~aAhaA","text_ar":"زَكَّاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he prospereth who purifieth it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, his soul]: sometimes it is God; as in [the saying in the Kur xxiv. 21,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal`kin~a A@ll~`ha yuzak~iY","text_ar":"وَلٰكِنَّ ا@للّٰهَ يُزَكِّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano ya$aA='u","text_ar":"مَنْ يَشَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But God purifieth whom He willeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and sometimes it is the Prophet; as in the saying [in the Kur ix. 104],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o mino A^amowaAlihimo SadaqapF tuTah~iruhumo","text_ar":"خُذْ مِنْ اَمْوَالِهِمْ صَدَقَةً تُطَهِّرُهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watuzak~iyhimo bihaA","text_ar":"وَتُزَكِّيهِمْ بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou, from their possessions, a poor-rate, whereby thou shalt cleanse them and purify them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"where (J says in the S) they say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuzak~iyhimo","text_ar":"تُزَكِّيهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuTah~iruhumo","text_ar":"تُطَهِّرُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and in the saying [in the Kur ii. 146],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yatoluw Ealayokumo A=yaAtinaA","text_ar":"يَتْلُو عَلَيْكُمْ ا=يَاتِنَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayuzak~iykumo","text_ar":"وَيُزَكِّيكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who reciteth to you our signs, and purifieth you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, accord. to what is said in the Kur ix. 104, i. e. because the act which it signifies is believed to purify the performer, or because it is believed to purify, or to occasion an increase of, the rest of his property,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zk~Y maAlahu","text_ar":"زكّى مَالَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n. as above, (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaAp","text_ar":"زَكَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poorrate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zk~Ahu","text_ar":"زكّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zk~Ahumo","text_ar":"زكّاهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaAp","text_ar":"زَكَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poor-rate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Mgh.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zak~ayotuhu","text_ar":"زَكَّيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I attributed to him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA='","text_ar":"زَكَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteousness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [And hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I praised him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zk~Y","text_ar":"زكّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosahu","text_ar":"نَفْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh,) inf. n. as above, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He praised himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh.) The doing this is forbidden in the Kur liii. 33. (Er-Rághib, TA.) Hence, also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazokiyapu Al$~uhuwdi","text_ar":"تَزْكِيَةُ الشُّهُودِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pronouncing the witnesses to be veracious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yuxas~iY wayuzak~iY","text_ar":"هُوَ يُخَسِّى وَيُزَكِّى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He plays, and says,"},{"kind":"text","text":"“"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is it even"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odd"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odd or even"},{"kind":"text","text":"]?” (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xsw","text_ar":"خسو"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he takes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holds, something in his hand, and says,"},{"kind":"text","text":"“"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is it even or odd"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odd or even"},{"kind":"text","text":"]?” (TA in the present art.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA","text_ar":"زَكَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.]"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n17936","headword_ar":"زَكَاةٌ","root":"zkw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":". or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zak`wpN","text_ar":"زَكٰوةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [accord. to El-Hareeree, to be written with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"when prefixed to a pronoun, and also in the dual number, (see De Sacy's Anthol. Gram. Arabe, p. 67 of the Arabic text,) but this rule I have not found to be generally observed, even in the best MSS., nor have I in the similar cases of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sal`wpN","text_ar":"صَلٰوةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay`wpN","text_ar":"حَيٰوةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (to which it is also applied,) in the best copies of the Kur-án,] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalapN","text_ar":"فَعَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e., originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakawapN","text_ar":"زَكَوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaqapN","text_ar":"صَدَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is one of its syns.]; a noun of the class of homonyms: (IAth, TA:) it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Increase,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"augmentation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Er-Rághib, TA,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA='N","text_ar":"زَكَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[mentioned in the first paragraph as an inf. n.], (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resulting from the blessing of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is [said to be] the primary meaning; and is considered as relating to the things of the present world and to those of the world to come. (Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Purity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.) And [particularly] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dryness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the earth or ground; which is its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purity from defilement."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Purification:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a meaning which it is said to have in the saying in the Kur [xxiii. 4],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@l~a*iyna humo lilz~ak`wpi faAEiluwna","text_ar":"وَا@لَّذِينَ هُمْ لِلزَّكٰوةِ فَاعِلُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAth, Mgh, Er-Rághib, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And who are acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"in their religious service"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for"},{"kind":"text","text":"God's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purification"},{"kind":"text","text":"of them; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for"},{"kind":"text","text":"their"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purification"},{"kind":"text","text":"of themselves: for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilz~ak`wp","text_ar":"لِلزَّكٰوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not here an objective complement of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEiluwna","text_ar":"فَاعِلُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"therein denoting the aim and the cause. (Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b4-  Also, [as being a mode of purification of oneself,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous, conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in this sense it has been expl. as used in the Kur xviii. 80: or as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteousness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA='N","text_ar":"زَكَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also] signifies. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Religious service;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being the means of purification: so [accord. to some] it signifies in the saying [in the Kur xix. 14],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHanaAnFA mino ladun~aA wazak`wpF","text_ar":"وَحَنَانًا مِنْ لَدُنَّا وَزَكٰوةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And"},{"kind":"text","text":"the disposition to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mercy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compassion, from us, and religious service"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Er-Rághib, TA:) or it here means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuhorap","text_ar":"طُهْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purification,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and [accord. to some, if we except the instances mentioned above in the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1241},{"kind":"text","text":"next two preceding sentences,] this is the only instance in the Kur-án in which it is used in any other sense than that which next follows. (Kull p. 199.) ―         -b5-  And [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poor-rate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"amount, of property, that is given therefrom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, IAth, Mgh, Msb, K, Er-Rághib, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as the due of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by its possessor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the poor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, Er-Rághib, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that he may purify it thereby:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, IAth, K, TA:) [in the S it is merely said that “ the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zak`wp","text_ar":"زَكٰوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of property is well known: ” the giving it is obligatory, provided that the property is of a certain amount, and has been in possession eleven months: the portion given varies according to the nature and amount of the property; but is generally a fortieth part thereof, or of its value; i. e. two and a half per cent.:] it is thus termed [for the reason assigned above; or] as being a cause of the hope of increase, (Msb, Er-Rághib, TA,) or as causing the soul, or person, to thrive, or grow, by means of good things and blessings [procured thereby], or for both of these reasons. (Er-Rághib, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaApu AlfiTori","text_ar":"زَكَاةُ الفِطْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The alms of the breaking of the fast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"given at the end of Ramadán,] is obligatory upon every person of the Muslims, the free and the slave, the male and the female, the young and the old, the poor and the rich; and purifies the faster from unprofitable and lewd discourse: it consists of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAE","text_ar":"صَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] of dates, or of barley, [or of raisins or some other ordinary kind of food,] or half that quantity of wheat. (El-Jámi' es-Sagheer, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaAp","text_ar":"زَكَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakawaAtN","text_ar":"زَكَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-  Also, [as being an attribution of purity or goodness or righteousness,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Praise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.) ―         -b7-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best, part of a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) on the authority of Aboo-'Alee. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IAth","TA","Msb","M","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}